## CODE QUALITY ‚Äî Polish Items

### QUALITY 1 ‚Äî Pervasive typos in identifiers
`addBoorkmark`, `addBoorkmarkSetvice`, `inserNotifPromise`, `inserLikePromise`, `paresedLimit`, `verfifyTurnstile`, `fetchind`, `loggendUserId`, `intiger`, `initaConfig`. These hurt readability and make grep unreliable.

### QUALITY 2 ‚Äî Inconsistent route naming
Old routes use verbs/camelCase (`addComment`, `getFollowsData`, `addBoorkmark`), newer routes use RESTful conventions (`/stories/:id/chapters`). Pick one style ‚Äî RESTful is the standard.

### QUALITY 3 ‚Äî Unnecessary multer on non-upload routes
`upload` middleware is applied to `POST /addComment`, `POST /addBoorkmark`, `POST /addFollows`, etc. ‚Äî routes that never handle file uploads. Adds unnecessary multipart parsing overhead.

### QUALITY 4 ‚Äî No `React.memo` anywhere
Zero `React.memo()` calls in the entire client. Feed cards rendering in lists would benefit significantly.

### QUALITY 5 ‚Äî 9 Google Fonts loaded, ~6 unused
`index.css` loads 9 font families. Inter, Nunito, Comfortaa, Patrick Hand, Shadows Into Light, and Sniglet don't appear in CSS variable definitions. Audit and remove unused ones ‚Äî each is a render-blocking request.

### QUALITY 6 ‚Äî CORS origins hardcoded
**`server.js:540`** ‚Äî CORS origins include `http://localhost:5173` and a Render staging URL. Move to environment variables.

### QUALITY 7 ‚Äî `cacheTime` ‚Üí `gcTime`
Several React Query usages use the deprecated `cacheTime` option. In v5 this is `gcTime`. It works now but will be removed.

### QUALITY 8 ‚Äî ESLint disables critical rules
`react-hooks/exhaustive-deps: 'off'` and `no-unused-vars: 'off'` mask real bugs (stale closures, dead code). No ESLint config exists for the server at all.

### QUALITY 9 ‚Äî No Prettier / code formatter
No `.prettierrc` or `.editorconfig`. Code formatting relies on discipline alone.

### QUALITY 10 ‚Äî LRU cache duplicated
LRU cache implementation is copy-pasted between `server.js` (lines 89-112) and `discoveryService.js` (lines 7-25). Extract to a shared utility.

